Bring a large #pot{} of water to a rapid boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Wash the @brown basmati rice{1%cup} under running water for ~{30%seconds} (important step!). Boil the rice for ~{25%minutes} until soft enough to eat. Drain the rice and put it back in the pot off the heat and cover with a #tea towel{}.

Peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and very thinly sliced) in half lengthways and then very thinly slice half of it into half moon shapes. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Then finely chop the @red chilli{1}(finely chopped) and roughly chop the @coriander{3%sprigs}(roughly chopped). Thinly slice the @celery stick{1}(thinly sliced) widthways and chop the @yellow pepper{1/2}(chopped into 3cm chunks). Peel the @ginger{1%thumb-size piece} using the edge of a #spoon{} and then very finely chop.

Slice the @aubergine{1/2}(sliced and chopped into 2-3cm chunks) in half lengthways then slice each half lengthways into four strips. Now chop widthways into 2-3cm chunks. Toss the aubergine chunks in the @cornflour{1%tbsp} together with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}.

Heat @oil{2%tsp} in a non-stick #frying pan{} on high heat. Once really hot, carefully add in the aubergine. Stir fry the aubergine for ~{5%minutes} while you toss the pan and add more oil if needed. Remove the aubergine from the pan and set to the side.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in the same frying pan and add in the onion, garlic, chilli and ginger. After ~{1%minute}, add the yellow pepper and cook for ~{2%minutes}.

Now add the @sugar snap peas{1/2%cup} and the celery and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Add @water{2%tbsp} and cover the pan. Leave to cook for another ~{2%minutes}.

Squeeze the juice of half the @lime{1/2}(juiced) into the @hoisin sauce{3%tbsp}. Take the lid off the stir-fry and add in the sauce together with the aubergine. Sprinkle over the chopped coriander and the @salted peanuts{2%tbsp}(chopped). Toss everything together for ~{1%minute} and then serve with the rice.